  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the end of three years from the date of this permission.\r\n\r\nReason: In order to comply with the provisions of Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).\r\n\r\n",
    "Condition : 2 - The development hereby permitted shall be carried out in accordance with the following approved plans:\r\n\r\nExisting drawings: P-100 Rev 1; P-200 Rev 1; P-210 Rev 1; P-211 Rev 1; P-212 Rev 1;\r\n\r\nProposed drawings: P-300 Rev 1; P-340 Rev 1; P-341 Rev 1; P-342 Rev 1; P-343 Rev 1; P-344 Rev 1;\r\n\r\nSupporting documents: Daylight and Sunlight Report prepared by Rights of Light Consulting dated 4 July 2023;  Design and Access Statement prepared by TG Studio dated 28.11.23; Planning and Heritage Statement prepared by DWD dated December 2023; Sustainability Statement prepared by DWD dated 05/02/2024; DWD Response to Public Comments dated 29/02/2024\r\n\r\nReason: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interest of proper planning.\r\n",
    "Condition : 3 - All new external work shall be carried out in materials that resemble, as closely as possible, in colour and texture those of the existing building, unless otherwise specified in the approved application. \r\n\r\nReason: To safeguard the appearance of the premises and the character of the immediate area in accordance with the requirements of policy D1 and D2  of the London Borough of Camden Local Plan 2017. \r\n",
    "Condition : 4 - Before the relevant part of the work is begun, detailed drawings, or samples of materials as appropriate, in respect of the following, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority: \r\n\r\na) Details including sections at 1:10 of all windows (including jambs, head and cill), ventilation grills, external doors and gates; \r\n\r\nb) Details of metal privacy screen to terrace (elevation and section at 1:20)  including details demonstrating how the screen would minimise climbing opportunities. \r\n\r\nc) Manufacturer's specification details of all facing materials (to be submitted to the Local Planning Authority) and samples of those materials (to be provided on site).    \r\n\r\nThe relevant part of the works shall be carried out in accordance with the details thus approved and all approved samples shall be retained on site during the course of the works. \r\n\r\nReason:  To safeguard the appearance of the premises and the character of the immediate area in accordance with the requirements of policy D1 and D2 of the London Borough of Camden Local Plan 2017.\r\n",
    "Condition : 5 - The development hereby approved shall achieve a maximum internal water use of 110litres/person/day. The dwelling/s shall not be occupied until the Building Regulation optional requirement has been complied with. \r\n\r\nReason: To ensure the development contributes to minimising the need for further water infrastructure in an area of water stress in accordance with Policies CC1, CC2, CC3 of the London Borough of Camden Local Plan 2017.\r\n",
    "Condition : 6 - Waste store\r\n \r\nThe waste stores hereby approved shall be provided prior to the first occupation of the development and permanently retained thereafter.\r\n\r\nReason: To ensure that sufficient provision for the storage and collection of waste has been made in accordance with the requirements of policy CC5 and A1 of the London Borough of Camden Local Plan 2017.",
    "Condition : 7 - Rooflight    \r\n\r\nPrior to first occupation, the approved rooflight (as shown on drawing P-343 Rev 1) shall be fitted with obscure glass and shall be retained and maintained as such thereafter. \r\n\r\nReason: In order to prevent overlooking of future occupants and to prevent light spill to neighbouring dwellings in accordance with the requirements of policies A1 and D1 of the London Borough of Camden Local Plan 2017.\r\n"
  ],
